{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The speech-to-text output preserves speaker labels so that the summary can attribute statements to specific attendees.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The core failure boundary is between modules: STT response parsing/normalization and summary input construction. A unit test on one function would miss real wiring issues (field-name mismatch, dropped diarization metadata). Real STT quality is not required to catch this specific preservation failure, so Agentic is not the minimum.","test_description":"Run the transcription-to-summary-input path with a realistic STT fixture that includes diarization/speaker labels (multiple speakers, overlapping turns). Assert speaker labels survive normalization and are present in the payload/context passed to summarization with correct utterance association.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.08,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The structured summary contains at least one action item for every attendee who was assigned a task during the meeting.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on semantic extraction/coverage from a real LLM output, which can vary across runs and prompts. Mocked LLM responses can hide the real failure (missing assignees/tasks) because they pre-bake ideal output.","test_description":"Use real meeting transcripts with known assigned tasks per attendee and call the real summarization model. Parse structured output and verify each attendee with an assigned task appears with at least one action item. Run repeated trials and evaluate pass-rate threshold to handle model variance.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.68,"Workflow":0.07}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Key decisions mentioned in the transcript appear in the \"decisions\" section of the summary, not buried in the narrative.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"This is a model-output quality/placement requirement, not just schema wiring. A deterministic mock would likely always place items correctly and miss real section-placement drift from the LLM.","test_description":"Feed transcripts containing explicit decision statements to the real summarization model. Assert those decisions are present in the dedicated `decisions` field/section and not only in free-form narrative text. Repeat across multiple runs/transcripts to detect non-deterministic placement failures.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.2,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.66,"Workflow":0.07}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"When the audio file is longer than 60 minutes, the service splits it into segments and processes them sequentially, merging the results into a single coherent summary.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This behavior spans multiple sequential processing steps with agentic dependence (segment-level transcription/summarization plus merge). Failures often emerge only across step boundaries (context loss, duplicated/missed items after merge), which single-step tests miss.","test_description":"Run an end-to-end long-audio case (>60 min) through real chunking/orchestration: segment creation, ordered per-segment processing, and final merge. Assert sequential processing order, complete segment coverage, and merged structured summary consistency (no dropped/duplicated key items across segment boundaries).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.28,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.22,"Workflow":0.4}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The full pipeline — upload audio, transcribe, summarize, deliver structured output — completes without manual intervention for a real meeting recording.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This is explicitly full-pipeline, multi-step, and includes real external services plus model-dependent outputs. Only a full workflow test can expose orchestration, retries/timeouts, handoff, and cross-step failure modes that mocks or isolated tests hide.","test_description":"Execute a production-like run on a real meeting recording through the actual upload, transcription API, summarization model, and output delivery path. Assert completion status, structured output contract validity, and absence of manual recovery actions/interventions.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.2,"Workflow":0.6}}]}
